The paper proposes a learning approach for automatically generating action models from noisy and disordered plan traces. This involves using a MAX-SAT framework for learning, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the use of natural language plan traces implies a connection to computational linguistics (cs.CL). The evaluation of the approach on both IPC domains and real-world datasets suggests a potential connection to robotics (cs.RO) and software engineering (cs.SE).
